&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a BIM Technician, you will play a key role in ensuring timely and accurate updates to our Master Floor Plans. In this role, you will have the opportunity to demonstrate creative problem-solving and work with your team to ensure accurate blueprints for the organization. The most rewarding aspect of this role is that you will help ensure we provide customers with a building experience that stays within the budget and on time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;You Will Thrive in This Role If You…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enjoy producing precise, detail-driven work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate clearly and collaborate well with others&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay organized and manage multiple tasks effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are excited to help drive the organization&#39;s transition from CAD to Revit and contribute to the evolution of our design and drafting processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embrace emerging technologies, including AI-powered tools, to improve efficiency, streamline workflows, and optimize processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adapt quickly to shifting priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Approach challenges with a solutions-focused mindset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;These skills will be used to:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and update residential master documentation and drawing sets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce accurate drawing revisions within established timelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain master files and related supporting materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in quality control reviews and complete required corrections&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support updates to exteriors, structural options, predetermined options, and related documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in analyzing field or production issues and help implement corrective actions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help communicate and support rollout of updates to lot‑specific production teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with team members across departments to complete assigned work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow established drafting, BIM, and documentation standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain awareness of required company systems, processes, and training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–3 years of experience in residential drafting, BIM, CAD, architectural documentation, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read and interpret residential construction documents and blueprints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of Revit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail, organization, and time‑management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in residential construction, drafting, architecture, construction management, or related fields&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Associate or bachelor’s degree in a relevant discipline preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Physical demands and work environment:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to communicate effectively with associates and customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to perform repetitive motions and use fine motor skills to operate standard office equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift and carry approximately 20–25 lbs. unassisted&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to sit for extended periods, with occasional reaching and standing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
